						<h3>Research</h3>
						<p>S3-Lab researchers developed the first web-based global carbon accounting tool (G-CAT) that can capture the regional and global carbon footprint on nationâ€™s production and consumption. This online decision making tool enables the users to conduct a detailed, global and supply chain-based carbon footprint analysis in a 5 steps.</p>
						<p> A Multi Region Input-Output (MRIO) analysis is used to develop the mathematical foundation of the tool. As a MRIO database, a first public World Input-Output Database (WIOD) is used in order to obtain an industry-by-industry multi-region input-output tables and emission factors for 40 countries distinguishing 35 sectors. This database provides time-series of world input-output tables for forty countries worldwide and a model for the rest-of-the-world, covering the period from 1995 to 2011. </p>
						<p>Using this tool, decision makers can evaluate the regional and global carbon footprint of a specific sector for a given year, estimate the scope-based carbon footprint, visualize the geographical distribution of carbon emissions worldwide and develop dynamic charts comparisons the sectors or countries and understand the contribution of upstream global supply chain to the net carbon footprint.</p>
